This product includes ideas and algorithmic patterns adapted from:

  - simonthum/git-sync (https://github.com/simonthum/git-sync)
    Released under CC0-1.0 (public domain dedication).
    Sync-loop sequencing and "check mode" semantics were studied and
    re-implemented in Rust.

  - tiddly-gittly/git-sync-js (https://github.com/tiddly-gittly/git-sync-js)
    Released under the MIT License.
    Copyright (c) tiddly-gittly contributors.
    The typed-error model and the granular GitStep progress enum informed
    crates/gfs-core/src/status.rs. No source code was copied.

  - GitJournal/git-auto-sync (https://github.com/GitJournal/git-auto-sync)
    Released under MIT/Apache-2.0-style permissive terms.
    Behaviour around foreground notification of conflicts informed the
    Conflict UI hand-off design.

The following projects were studied as architectural references only;
no code from them is included in this distribution:

  - SparkleShare (https://github.com/hbons/SparkleShare) — GPLv3 / LGPLv3.
    The five-state tray-icon vocabulary (Idle / Syncing / Paused / Conflict
    / Error) and the per-folder tray submenu pattern are concepts; the
    implementation here is independent.

  - obsidian-git (https://github.com/Vinzent03/obsidian-git) — MIT.
    Inspired the dual-timer model (debounced commit + interval pull) but
    no code was copied.

All other dependencies are listed in Cargo.lock / pnpm-lock.yaml with
their original licenses preserved. License compliance is enforced via
`cargo-deny` (see `deny.toml`).
